a mixer tap (= one in which hot and cold water can be mixed together before it comes out of the pipe)

data.chText: 擅长 / 不擅长交际的人
data.enText: a person who finds it easy/difficult to talk to people they do not know, for example at a party

tr: a kitchen utensil that is used for mixing foods
electronic equipment that mixes two or more input signals to give a single output signal
club soda or fruit juice used to mix with alcohol
a party of people assembled to promote sociability and communal activity

value.def: A mixer is a machine used for mixing things together.
A mixer is a non-alcoholic drink such as fruit juice that you mix with strong alcohol such as gin.
If you say that someone is a good mixer, you mean that they are good at talking to people and making friends.

example.ex: Cooper was a good mixer, he was popular.
example.tran: 库珀擅长交际，人缘很好。

value.def: A mixer is a piece of equipment that is used to make changes to recorded music or film.

example.tran: 有3个频道的音频混合器
